{{Infobox organization |name = Terres Inovia |motto = Agricultural sciences in motion (''L'Agronomie en mouvement'') |image= |type = research institute |formation = 2015 |location = [[Paris]], [[France]] (head office) and 16 research stations in France |leader_name = Bernard de Verneuil |leader_title = President |purpose = [[applied research]] |budget = |staff = {{formatnum:137}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.acta.asso.fr/le-reseau/acces-par-institut/detail-institut/i/institut/detail/cetiom.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-08-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150926215421/http://www.acta.asso.fr/le-reseau/acces-par-institut/detail-institut/i/institut/detail/cetiom.html |archivedate=2015-09-26 |df= }}</ref> |homepage = http://www.terresinovia.fr/about-terres-inovia/ }}
'''Terres Inovia''' is a French [[agriculture|agricultural]] research institute carrying out [[applied research]] on oilseed plants and [[protein crop]]. It was created in June, 2015<ref>http://www.terre-net.fr/actualite-agricole/economie-social/article/le-cetion-renomme-terres-inovia-202-110312.html</ref> by merging: * the CETIOM, the French research institute on oilseed crops; * the UNIP, the French research institute on protein crops.
Terres Inovia main tasks are to conduct research and to disseminate technical knowledge to farmers. It has partnerships with other French research institutes such as [[Institut national de la recherche agronomique|INRA]] and [[Arvalis Institut du Végétal]];<ref>http://www.terresinovia.fr/about-terres-inovia/</ref> also, it participates to European research projects (e.g. the Feed-a-Gene project<ref>http://www.feed-a-gene.eu/organisation/terres-inovia</ref>). The crops studied are: * oilseed crops: ** [[rapeseed]] ** [[helianthus|sunflower]] ** [[soybean]] ** [[flax]] (especially for production of [[linseed oil]]) * protein crops: ** [[pea]] ** [[vicia faba|faba bean]] ** [[lupinus|lupin]] * [[hemp]].
